This paper involves building computational models to predict the risk of mortality for patients with acute myocardial infarction (AMI) using electronic health records (EHRs) data. The use of deep learning models and word embedding features from free-text discharge summaries suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of structured clinical data from MIMIC-III and the impact of different combinations of features extracted from structured and/or unstructured data suggest that this paper could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
